{2060}{}{Alright, partner. I'm ready for a new case.}
{2070}{}{Another case closed, partner. }
{2080}{}{Alright, partner. I'm ready for another case.}
{2090}{}{Let's do this.}
{2100}{}{[Throw the killer's mask on Detective Deckard's desk]}
{2110}{}{Hey Deckard. Looks like I got to keep my badge after all. Did you hear?}
{2120}{}{Sorry, didn't mean to bother you.}
{3000}{}{I'm detective Thomas Deckard, what do you want?}
{3010}{}{Oh, nothing. Just looking around.}
{4000}{}{If you've seen the things I've seen, you'd drink too. Now get the fuck out of my office.}
{5000}{}{[Detective Deckard doesn't even look up] I know who you are. You're a scared little kid that's about to get @sex@|himself||herself| killed.}
{5010}{}{Killed? Then who'll save you people?}
{6000}{}{[Detective Deckard doesn't even flinch] People don't need saving. They just need the ability to wake up every morning, go to work, and come home to jerk off. The only thing people care about is how much money they're working for, and how safely they can beat it.}
{6010}{}{[Say nothing]}
{6020}{}{Why did you become a cop?}
{6030}{}{What the hell are you talking about?}
{6040}{}{Are you drunk?}
{7000}{}{[He says nothing]}
{7010}{}{[Say nothing]}
{8000}{}{[He takes another sip of Rotgut] Fuck you, punk. You think you're a hero? Save this! [He throws you a case file. Inside the file is dozens of pictures of naked young girls that have been brutally murdered. Their breasts have been hacked up with a sharp object, and their entrails are smeared across their bodies. Your eyes widen in horror, as you stand there, perfectly still] }
{8010}{}{*Gasp!*}
{9000}{}{[You fall back into a chair and do nothing. Detective Deckard puts the photos away and lights up a cigarette. You take his bottle of Rotgut, pour yourself a glass and start drinking]}
{9010}{}{We're going to need more bourbon.}
{10000}{}{[Detective Deckard pulls out another bottle of whiskey from his desk, and says] Rollo Tomasi.}
{10010}{}{That some kind of joke?}
{11000}{}{[Detective Deckard sighs] No, it's what I call a suspect that gets away with it. Rollo Tomasi... My father was killed by from random robber when I was a teen. They never found him, so I invented that name as a reminder. There's only ever been one "Rollo Tomasi" and I'll die before we let another one slip.}
{11010}{}{That's too bad about your father, sorry.}
{12000}{}{[He takes a sip of Rotgut] Don't worry about it, a long time ago. Been a cop long enough to feel like I got the world back. You're from a vault, I hear. You got any family? [Something inside of you breaks]}
{12010}{}{[Give him the limp, blank, unfocused gaze of a battle-weary soldier]}
{13000}{}{[Detective Deckard seems to understand] Me too, kid. It goes away, I guess. But you got the scar of the hero now, don't ever forget what it means, @sex@|boy.||girl.| Only the good people suffer from war, the rest just enjoy it too much.}
{13010}{}{[Stare out a thousand yards away] I didn't think it would be so bad. It's not what I've seen that scares me the most. It's what you have.}
{14000}{}{[Detective Deckard pats you on the back, and says] You're just going through the phases, it happens to a lot of us. You'd think if you'd be tough enough to become a cop, you could handle the harsh reality of crime, but *this* is normal. A lot of people piss their pants, or cry after they kill someone. Even if their opponent was a scumbag. }
{14010}{}{Yeah well, tears won't save you in the line of duty. Enough of this crap! Who the fuck's been hacking up these broads?}
{15000}{}{[He laughs] There's your balls! Alright @sex@|boy||girlie|, let's go solve a real crime. You ever hear about the boogeyman? Some asshole that hides in your closet, or under the bed and snatches you away from the world just after he wakes you from a sweet dream?}
{15010}{}{I'm the boogeyman. Only thing I'm really starting to fear.}
{16000}{}{[Detective Deckard sits back and throws off his Fedora] You probably can't even dance. Well, there's a real boogeyman going around the NCR killing people at night. We've managed to stop the word from getting out, but every couple of a nights we wake up to find a dead woman in town. At first we thought we were all over it, thinking we'd solve it within a few hours. But the bodies kept pilling up, even after we had people in jail. }
{16010}{}{Sounds like a serial killer.}
{17000}{}{[Detective Deckard looks worried] Sounds like a smart killer. Clearly whoever they are has been framing people, leaving us false clues, and making us lock up the wrong people. It's fucking embarrasing, but we keep playing along, almost like it's some kind of ransom. }
{17010}{}{Shit. So this is bad, isn't it?}
{18000}{}{[Detective Deckard looks worried, but lights up a cigarette and starts to brighten up] It's really bad. But you, YOU my friend, you'll figure it out. I bet my ass on it. }
{18010}{}{Yeah... I guess, man. Whatever.}
{19000}{}{[He laughs] You want to see the pictures again?}
{19010}{}{Fuck no. Okay, okay. I'm going to solve this, don't you worry. Even if it kills me emotionally, I'll put an end to this madness!}
{20000}{}{[Detective Deckard puts the case file away] That a @sex@|boy||girl|! Alright, hero! You come back when you're ready to begin. It'll take a few hours to get this done, but just come back when you're truly ready.}
{20010}{}{Alright. I'll let you know.}
{21000}{}{[The sun dies, and you and Detective Deckard hit the streets. A cold wind blows, but the rain will never stop. You're soaked by the time you're finished your patrol] That's the generic run. We walk around, have a gander at the flock and plan the next move. Where to next, partner?}
