{26010}{}{[Continue your patrol]}
{26020}{}{[Continue your patrol]}
{27000}{}{[Downtown is quiet, not a single soul walks these streets. It isn't even eerie. Just wet, and full of rain. It's starting to burn your eyes] }
{27010}{}{[Continue your patrol]}
{27020}{}{[Continue your patrol]}
{28000}{}{[You and the Detective walk into Dusty's Cantina. Upon entry, Deckard sits at the bar and starts to talk to Dusty. You look around the room but don't see much of interest]}
{28010}{}{[Continue your patrol]}
{28020}{}{[Continue your patrol]}
{29000}{}{[Upon walking into Mira's bar, the crowd falls quiet. Looks like they're pretty afraid of Deckard. The room is absolute silence]}
{29010}{}{[Continue your patrol]}
{29020}{}{[Continue your patrol]}
{30000}{}{[You can hear the sounds of screams coming from the hospital! But as you approach you realize it's only the Doc performing surgery. There's nothing else of interest here]}
{30010}{}{[Continue your patrol]}
{30020}{}{[Continue your patrol]}
{31000}{}{[You hear a bloody scream coming from the distance!]}
{31010}{}{Deckard! Did you hear that? Let's move!}
{32000}{}{[Detective Deckard starts running beside you] Let's go, kid!}
{32010}{}{[Run out into the distance!]}
{33000}{}{[You follow the sounds of murder for what seems like hours. You and Detective Deckard run through several series of alleyways while chasing the sounds of someone dragging a body. After a few more moments of running you begin to see a faint trail of blood. As you continue pursuing the strange sounds, the trace of blood begins to get thicker] Get your gun ready, kid! [says Detective Deckard]}
{33010}{}{[Pull out your .44 Magnum]}
{34000}{}{[You and the Detective turn the corner and find a dead young girl, still dressed but with her throat slit. There is nobody else around, but a small trail of blood leading out into the darkness]}
{34010}{}{Let's go chase some shadows, Deckard!}
{35000}{}{[Deckard grabs you before you run off] Hold up! Let me radio this in. I'm not running out there without backup.}
{35010}{}{Nonsense! I'm your backup! Let's go! [Take off running]}
{36000}{}{[Deckard looks pissed] Damnit, kid! You're going to get yourself killed!}
{36010}{}{[Follow the trail of blood]}
{37000}{}{[If you'd like to do this mission in Turn Based mode, type /combatmode tb before hitting continue! This will be extremely challenging!]}
{37010}{}{You can't run from me!}
{38000}{}{[Detective Deckard spits out his whiskey and jumps out of his chair] Holy shit! You did it! Have a cigar partner! [He hands you a cigar and pours you a shot of Rotgut]  }
{38010}{}{[Watch the rain fall down as you smoke and drink]}
{39000}{}{[My dad used to tell stories about the outside world. Things I can no longer remember. But I remember one story he used to tell. One saying particularly stuck: It's not given to people to judge what's right or wrong. People have eternally been mistaken and will always be mistaken, and in nothing more than in what they consider right and wrong. Some rise by sin, some by virtue fall. If the end brings me out all right, what is said against me wonвЂ™t amount to anything. If the end brings me out wrong, ten angels swearing I was right would make no difference]}
{39010}{}{[Smile]}
{40000}{}{[Detective Deckard smiles too] What's next for you partner?}
{40010}{}{Guess I'll take a break, then go talk to Detective Gallows. Get to the bottom of this attempted assassination. }
{41000}{}{[The rain starts to die down. You wonder how long that will last? Detective Deckard shakes your hand, and says] Make me proud, partner. Maybe we'll get ourselves another case to work on real soon. Good luck figuring the next one out.}
{41010}{}{It was a pleasure working with you, Detective Deckard. I'll see you around.}
{42000}{}{Of course, @pname@. Gallows wants to buy you a round of drinks some day. She's been talking about you a lot, ever since you talked to her actually. But that's not important. What's important is that you're my new partner now, and we've got a list full of names to bring in. Dead or alive. I'll split the list in half with you. Just let me know when you want to go do your own house call. That's it, Detective. Just sitting around.}
{42010}{}{Great. Thanks, Deckard. I'll let you know soon}
{43000}{}{Got some more scumbags from the East stepping up in the NCR. Trying to pollute the area, I reckon. Already gave em' warnings. No sense in bringing em' in just to hang. As long as they're still alive the rail lines just ain't safe. On top of that, we got Powder Gangers moving in as well. No use in identifying which gang you're stopping. Just go to the ruins of Ridgecrest, and read em' their rights when they're dead.}
{43010}{}{They'll never know what hit them.}
{44000}{}{Are you ready to leave now? [Type /combatmode tb to play this mission in Turn Based mode]}
{44010}{}{Yes.}
{44020}{}{No, I'll be back.}
{45000}{}{Good luck, partner.}
{46000}{}{Sounds about right, Detective. Nothing stops you. I bet those fuckers from the East sure regret coming to California now. Good work. I've got more cases if you want them. Same thing. Rail Raiders, and Powder Gangers. Just let me know when you're ready.}
{46010}{}{Will do, partner.}
{47000}{}{This city, @pname@... it eats away at the justice we try to provide. Every day another cop goes dirty. Call it drugs, greed, or lust, it doesn't matter. I need you to weed out another.  }
{47010}{}{I know the drill. I'll start asking questions.}
{48000}{}{Don't disappoint the NCR... again.}
{49000}{}{I heard. You do good work, kid. I'm proud of you for doing the right thing, and NCR thanks you.}
{49010}{}{My people try, sir. Well... some of them.}
{50000}{}{As long as they keep trying, we'll have tomorrow to look forward to. A world with much less sorrow.}
{50010}{}{We'll see, sir. For now, I'll be heading over to Junktown and represent the NCR.}
{51000}{}{Do what you do best, @pname@.}
